{
  "text": "High-performance liquid chromatography. Sample preparation. After mixing the TMZ solution with a thrombin solution, 0.5 mL of this solution and 0.5 mL of fibrinogen solution were admixed in 12-well plates (Corning Inc., New York, NY, USA) and left for a few minutes at room temperature until completely solidified. The wells were then filled with 1 mL of phosphate-buffered saline (PBS), which was exchanged every 24 h. Samples were collected at 24-h intervals (24-168 h). Sample preparation was as previously described. [CITATION_1] Sample aliquots (40 lL) were injected into HPLC columns for analysis.",
